{
  "stem": "9538.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We were allowed to take a hundredweight of clothes with us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And how carefully we weighed everything, that we had not an ounce more, or not a gram more than the hundred--",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Each of us.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there, I must say again that neighbors, at night, they had jumpers knitted for us, you know, warm clothing that was all put into these suitcases.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At that time, the Jews already had their own identity cards with a big J on it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we got-- the women got the additional name of Sarah.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I was Ruth Sarah Heilbronn.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My mother was Caroline Sarah Heilbronn.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the men got the extra name of Israel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My father was Wilhelm Israel Heilbronn.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So wherever you gave the name, even if you didn't look Jewish-- but you had to give your correct name-- Ruth Sarah Heilbronn, Wilhelm Israel Heilbronn--",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--so the authorities knew that here we got a Jew.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we had suitcases with our names on it, with Riga on it, and the date, you know, also with Israel and Sarah.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we allowed, each of us, to take a rucksack and hand luggage.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So on the day of the 10th of-- on the morning of the 10th of December, '45-- is-- '41, it was a Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I told you before, my parents were very Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had to go to the town hall.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there, we were about eight of us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Only eight of us were deported.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were the first ones-- a family by the name of Grunberg and their daughter, Gerda; and an uncle and aunt of mine, Josef and Rosa Heilbronn, which had no children.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
